The Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Minister, Muhammad Musa Bello, has condoled with the family of the former state chairman of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) Alhaji Yahaya Yunusa Suleiman. Bello, who was represented by the chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in the territory, Alhaji Abdulmalik Usman, who led a delegation to the deceased residence in Yangoji yesterday, expressed shock and sadness over the death of the deceased. He said the death of the former state PDP chairman who later defected to the APC prior to the general election was quite a great shock to the entire party. He described the late PDP chairman as a great politician who has made great impact on the political space of the FCT, praying for his soul to rest in peace. The minister urged the deceased family to see the death as natural, while also praying for God to give the family the fortitude to bear the loss. Among those in the minister’s delegation are; the former House of Representatives member, Alhaji Zakari Angulu Dobi, state APC Secretary, Nuhu Angama, chieftain of APC, Alhaji Musa Tanko Abari and other FCT APC executives. Minister condoles ex-reps member over father’s death Former Osun PDP chairman dies at 59 Aduda, Ona of Abaji condole with late Senator Yakwo’s family